<br>
Many reasons for my decision to embark on this journey could be given... similar to why other wolves have left the den in search of new experiences.  It does not make it easier however.  I've found allies for this journey, though nothing like the family that I have come to know here.  But, alas, I have my own goals at the moment, and they do not seem to mesh with those of the pack.  <br>
<br>
My brother Zynk, whom some of you have met, will stay with the pack in my absence if possible.  He hopes to have many more adventures with the wolves.<br>
<br>
Battle can make one grow weary, and long for home as time passes...  When that time comes I would be content to return home to the pack, and offer guidance to the cubs, if the elders would permit that.  but until that time, you are all in my thoughts and my /friends.<br>
<br>
*sniffs the wind, raises his head and howls at the moon above*<br>
<br>
